title: Readout of Vice President Biden’s Meeting with Members of the New Zealand Labour Party | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House
Office of the Vice President


For Immediate Release
July 21, 2016

 



Readout of Vice President Biden’s Meeting with Members of the New Zealand Labour Party





	Vice President Biden met today with leading members of the opposition Labour Party in Auckland. They affirmed the shared values, deepening partnership, and growing economic ties between the United States and New Zealand.  They also discussed the importance of a rules-based international order and exchanged views on a range of regional and global issues.
